This paper discusses cloud-native architectures and the services offered by cloud vendors, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper focuses on cloud infrastructure and its services. The second likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as the paper discusses the functionality of cloud services and their billing models. The third likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper discusses the design approaches of cloud services. The fourth likely category is cs.DB (Databases) as the paper discusses the database services offered by cloud vendors. The fifth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses machine learning services offered by cloud vendors.
